# RoboLedger V5.2.14: ATI Metadata Line & Layout Standardization

Implementing high-fidelity metadata display and standardizing UI card layouts to match the V5 design specification.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **ATI Format Integration**: I will replace the current Action Bar metrics with a monospace "ATI Line" in the header card. This will display `ACCOUNT: **** 1234 • TYPE: VISA BUSINESS • PERIOD: FEB 2024` for the selected account.

## Proposed Changes

### UI Logic (app.js)
- **renderTransactionsRestored**:
  - Standardize `header-card` inline padding to `12px 20px`.
  - Remove `cloudy-metric` blocks from `v5-action-bar`.
  - Re-align action bar icons horizontally.
  - Inject the ATI Metadata Line into the header text area when an account is selected.
  - Apply `font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace` and `text-transform: uppercase` to the ATI line.

### Metadata Persistence (ledger.core.js / app.js)
- Update mock `activeAcc` properties to include `accountNumber`, `accountType`, and `period` to support the initial UI render.

### Styling (system.css)
- Refine `.v5-ati-line` to use a monospace font stack and adjusted letter-spacing for forensic clarity.
- Ensure `.cloudy-right-group` in the action bar enforces horizontal alignment for all buttons.

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
1. **Layout Check**: Verify that the Header Card, Action Bar, and Switcher Bar all have identical height/padding "sizing".
2. **Metrics Removal**: Confirm the balance and transaction count are removed from the action bar.
3. **ATI Verification**: Select different accounts and verify the Monospace ATI line updates with correct formatted data.
4. **Icon Alignment**: Confirm Search, Popout, and Settings buttons are in a clean horizontal line.

